help.markdown:
exec/spawn with user input is the canonical command-injection vector. An MCP client can craft arguments that break out of the shell context and run arbitrary commands on the server host.

**Bad**
```ts
import { exec } from "node:child_process";
export default async ({ host }) => exec(`ping ${host}`);
```

**Good**
```ts
import { execFile } from "node:child_process";
export default async ({ host }) => execFile("ping", [host]);
```

Synchronous I/O blocks Node's event loop. When multiple tool calls run concurrently on the same server, a single readFileSync stalls every in-flight request.

**Bad**
```ts
import { readFileSync } from "fs";
export default async () => readFileSync("data.json", "utf8");
```

**Good**
```ts
import { readFile } from "fs/promises";
export default async () => await readFile("data.json", "utf8");
```
